Three Tshwane University of Technology (TUT) students are due to appear in the Specialised Commercial Crime Court on Thursday for allegedly taking R40 000 &#8216;bribe&#8217;.The three including one TUT SRC member and former TUT students are believed to have duped a security company to pay a bribe to win a contract to be service provider for Tshwane University of Technology, spokesperson Brigadier Hangwani Mulaudzi said.The suspects are believed to be between the ages of 25 and 30, were arrested shortly after after anti-corruption unit of the police was alerted to a drop off of R40 000 by the security company to the three.-TNA Reporter